{"title_page": "Nuvvu Naaku Nachav", "text_new": "{{short description|2001 Telugu film by K. Vijaya Bhaskar}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Nuvvu Naaku Nachchaav\n| image          = Nuvvu Naaku Nachav.jpg\n| image_size     = \n| caption        = Theatrical poster\n| director       = [[K. Vijaya Bhaskar]]\n| producer       = [[Sravanthi Ravi Kishore]]\n| writer         = [[Trivikram Srinivas]]<br>{{small|(story / dialogues)}}\n| screenplay     = K. Vijaya Bhaskar\n| starring       = [[Daggubati Venkatesh|Venkatesh]]<br>[[Aarthi Agarwal]]\n| music          = [[Saluri Koteswara Rao|Koti]]\n| cinematography = K. Ravindra Babu\n| editing        = [[A. Sreekar Prasad]]\n| studio         = [[Sri Sravanthi Movies]]<br />[[Suresh Productions]] {{small|(presents)}}\n| distributor    = Bollywood\n| released       = {{Film date|2001|09|06|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 181 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Telugu\n| budget         =\n| gross          =\n}}\n\n'''''Nuvvu Naaku Nachav''''' ({{lang-en|I Like You|italics=yes}}) is a 2001 [[Telugu Cinema|Telugu]] [[romantic comedy]] film produced by [[Sravanthi Ravi Kishore]] under the [[Sri Sravanthi Movies]] company, directed by [[K. Vijaya Bhaskar]]. It stars [[Daggubati Venkatesh|Venkatesh]] and [[Aarthi Agarwal]]. The music was composed by [[Saluri Koteswara Rao|Koti]]. The film was recorded as a \"blockbuster\" at the box office.<ref>http://www.telugusquare.com/birthday-special-venkatesh-hit-and-flop-films-ratio/#</ref> It was remade in Kannada as ''[[Gowramma]]'', starring [[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]] and [[Ramya]]; in Tamil as ''[[Vaseegara (film)|Vaseegara]]'', starring [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] and in Bengali as ''[[Majnu (Bengali Movie)|Majnu]]'', directed by [[Rajiv Kumar Biswas|Rajib]], starring [[Hiran Chatterjee|Hiran]] and [[Srabanti Chatterjee|Shrabanti]]. It was the highest-grossing film in Venkatesh Daggubati's career. The Telugu version received the state [[Nandi Award for Akkineni Award for Best Home-viewing Feature Film]]. This is the first film starring [[Aarthi Agarwal]] in Telugu movies.\n\n== Plot ==\nVenky (Venkatesh) is a graduate from Anakapalli. He goes to Hyderabad to attend the engagement ceremony of Nandini (Agarwal), daughter of Murthy ([[Prakash Raj]]). Murthy is a childhood friend of his father Sekharam ([[Chandra Mohan (Telugu actor)|Chandra Mohan]]).\n\nNandu is about to be engaged to a software professional from the USA. Venky helps the family in arrangements and soon bonds with everyone. He also has petty fights with Nandu. The relationship starts with hatred and turns into friendship. On the request of Sekharam, Murthy helps Venky in securing a job. Nandu confesses her love for Venky to him. Venky, who does not want to spoil the relationship between their parents, decides to leave the house, but Murthy goes to the railway station and talks to Venky, which makes Venky return. On his return, Nandu stops talking to him. When Venky accompanies Nandu and Pinky (Nandu's cousin) to Nandu's friend Asha's wedding, sparks fly between them. Even though Venky is also in love with Nandu, he does not express it and pretends that he did not have any feelings for Nandu. When they return, it is time for Nandu's wedding. Venky takes the onus of running the show of marriage. The demure Nandu is shattered. Circumstances lead to everyone finding out about Venky and Nandu. What follows, and how Nandu and Venky end up together, forms the climax of the story.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n* [[Daggubati Venkatesh|Venkatesh]] as Venky\n* [[Aarthi Agarwal]] as Nandini / Nandu(Voice dubbed by [[Savitha Reddy]])\n* [[Prakash Raj]] as Srinivasa Murthy\n* [[Sudha (Telugu actress)|Sudha]] as Lakshmi\n* [[Sudeepa Pinky]] as Pinky, Nandu's Cousin\n* [[Brahmanandam]] as Photographer\n* [[Sunil (actor)|Sunil]] as Banthi\n* [[Tanikella Bharani]] as Ashok\n* [[Chandra Mohan (Telugu actor)|Chandra Mohan]] as Shekaram\n* [[M. S. Narayana]] as Chanti\n* [[Babloo Prithiveeraj]] as Mohan\n* [[Shiju]] as Prasad, Nandu's fianc\u00e9\n* [[Shankar Melkote|Melkote]] as M.D.\n* [[Babu Mohan]] as Prasad's relative\n* [[Mallikarjuna Rao (actor)|Mallikarjuna Rao]] as Prasad's relative\n* [[Ananth Babu|Ananth]] as Asha's uncle\n* [[Chitti Babu Punyamurthula|Chitti Babu]] as Priest\n* [[Bandla Ganesh]] as Mohan's friend\n* [[Giridhar]] as Venky's friend\n* [[KK Sarma]] as Priest\n* [[Asha Saini]] as Asha\n* [[Suhasini Maniratnam|Suhasini]] as Sujatha\n* [[Sri Lakshmi (actress)|Sri Lakshmi]] as Asha's aunty\n* [[Hema (actress)|Hema]] as Padma\n* [[Padma Jayanthi]] as Prasad's mother\n* [[Kalpana Rai]] as Cook\n}}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Nuvvu Naaku Nachchav\n| type       = film\n| artist     = [[Saluri Koteswara Rao|Koti]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 2001\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = Soundtrack\n| length     = 29:17\n| label      = [[Aditya Music]]\n| producer   = [[Saluri Koteswara Rao|Koti]]\n| prev_title = [[Naalo Unna Prema]]\n| prev_year  = 2001\n| next_title = [[Adhipathi]]\n| next_year  = 2001\n}}\n\nMusic composed by [[Saluri Koteswara Rao|Koti]]. Music released on ADITYA Music Company. The song \"Okkasari Cheppaleva\" is based on the [[Robert Miles]] song [[Fable (Robert Miles song)|\"Fable\"]].\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed =\n| headline =\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 29:17\n| all_writing =\n| all_lyrics =\n| all_music =\n| title1  = Unna Mata Cheppaneevu\n| lyrics1 = [[Sirivennela Sitaramasastri]]\n| extra1  = [[Tippu (singer)|Tippu]], [[Harini (singer)|Harini]]\n| length1 = 4:43\n\n| title2  = O Navvu Chalu\n| lyrics2 = Sirivennela Sitaramasastri\n| extra2  = [[Shankar Mahadevan]]\n| length2 = 4:48\n\n| title3  = Aakasam Dhigi Vachi\n| lyrics3 = Sirivennela Sitaramasastri\n| extra3  = [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam|S. P. Balu]]\n| length3 = 5:10\n\n| title4  = Naa Chupe Ninu\n| lyrics4 = Sirivennela Sitaramasastri\n| extra4  = [[K. S. Chithra|Chitra]], Sriram Prabhu\n| length4 = 4:15\n\n| title5  = O Priyathama\n| lyrics5 = [[Bhuvanachandra]]\n| extra5  = S. P. Balu\n| length5 = 5:17\n\n| title6  = Okkasari Cheppaleva \n| lyrics6 = Sirivennela Sitaramasastri\n| extra6  = Chitra, [[Kumar Sanu]]\n| length6 = 5:11\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe film was released with 113 prints in 147 centres.<ref name=\"idlebrain.com\">[http://idlebrain.com/trade/records/nnn.html Cycle Stand - Telugu Cinema Records - Nuvvu Naaku Chav - Jayam Manadera<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929083244/http://idlebrain.com/trade/records/nnn.html |date=29 September 2007 }}</ref>\n\nAbout Trivikram's work on ''Nuvvu Naaku Nachav'', Fullhyd.com wrote, \"The highlights of the film are all the original humour and the subtlety in approach so alien to Tollywood. The dialogue writer, Trivikram Srinivas, is perhaps the real hero in this one.\" He is popularly known among Telugu audiences as \"''Maatala Maantrikudu''\" meaning \"Wizard of words\" for his crisp dialogue writing.\n\n== Box-office ==\nThe film had collected a distributors' share of Rs.180 million in its complete theatrical run.<ref>http://www.idlebrain.com/celeb/starhomes/venky/boxoffice.html</ref> and Rs.26.3 million in its opening week.<ref name=\"idlebrain.com\"/>\nIt was the third highest grossing Telugu film of all time, at its release.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n\nThe film had a 50-day run in 93 centres<ref>[http://idlebrain.com/trade/tsynop/tradestory24.html Cycle Stand - Telugu Cinema Trade Story<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and a 100-day run in 57 centres.<ref>[http://idlebrain.com/trade/tsynop/tradestory32.html Cycle Stand - Telugu Cinema Trade Story<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> It had a 175-day run in three centres.<ref>[http://www.cinegoer.com/venky175.htm CineGoer.com - Box-Office Records And Collections - Venkatesh's 175-Day Centres List<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070212224008/http://www.cinegoer.com/venky175.htm |date=12 February 2007 }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=0311594|title=Nuvvu Naaku Nachav}}\n\n{{Nandi Award for Best Home Viewing Feature Film}}\n{{K. Vijaya Bhaskar}}\n{{Trivikram Srinivas}}\n\n[[Category:Telugu-language films]]\n[[Category:2001 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Telugu films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Films set in Hyderabad, India]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Hyderabad, India]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:2000s romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Koti]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2001 Telugu film by K. Vijaya Bhaskar}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Nuvvu Naaku Nachchaav\n| image          = Nuvvu Naaku Nachav.jpg\n| image_size     = \n| caption        = Theatrical poster\n| director       = [[K. Vijaya Bhaskar]]\n| producer       = [[Sravanthi Ravi Kishore]]\n| writer         = [[Trivikram Srinivas]]<br>{{small|(story / dialogues)}}\n| screenplay     = K. Vijaya Bhaskar\n| starring       = [[Daggubati Venkatesh|Venkatesh]]<br>[[Aarthi Agarwal]]\n| music          = [[Saluri Koteswara Rao|Koti]]\n| cinematography = K. Ravindra Babu\n| editing        = [[A. Sreekar Prasad]]\n| studio         = [[Sri Sravanthi Movies]]<br />[[Suresh Productions]] {{small|(presents)}}\n| distributor    = Bollywood\n| released       = {{Film date|2001|09|06|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 181 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Telugu\n| budget         =\n| gross          =\n}}\n\n'''''Nuvvu Naaku Nachav''''' ({{lang-en|I Like You|italics=yes}}) is a 2001 [[Telugu Cinema|Telugu]] [[romantic comedy]] film produced by [[Sravanthi Ravi Kishore]] under the [[Sri Sravanthi Movies]] company, directed by [[K. Vijaya Bhaskar]]. It stars [[Daggubati Venkatesh|Venkatesh]] and [[Aarthi Agarwal]]. The music was composed by [[Saluri Koteswara Rao|Koti]]. The film was recorded as a \"blockbuster\" at the box office.<ref>http://www.telugusquare.com/birthday-special-venkatesh-hit-and-flop-films-ratio/#</ref> It was remade in Kannada as ''[[Gowramma]]'', starring [[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]] and [[Ramya]]; in Tamil as ''[[Vaseegara (film)|Vaseegara]]'', starring [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] and in Bengali as ''[[Majnu (Bengali Movie)|Majnu]]'', directed by [[Rajiv Kumar Biswas|Rajib]], starring [[Hiran Chatterjee|Hiran]] and [[Srabanti Chatterjee|Shrabanti]]. It was the highest grossing film in Venkatesh Daggubati's career. The Telugu version received the state [[Nandi Award for Akkineni Award for Best Home-viewing Feature Film]]. This is the first film starring [[Aarthi Agarwal]] in telugu movies.\n\n== Plot ==\nVenky (Venkatesh) is a graduate from Anakapalli. He goes to Hyderabad to attend the engagement ceremony of Nandini (Agarwal), daughter of Murthy ([[Prakash Raj]]). Murthy is a childhood friend of his father Sekharam ([[Chandra Mohan (Telugu actor)|Chandra Mohan]]).\n\nNandu is about to be engaged to a software professional from the USA. Venky helps the family in arrangements and soon bonds with everyone. He also has petty fights with Nandu. The relationship starts with hatred and turns into friendship. On the request of Sekharam, Murthy helps Venky in securing a job. Nandu confesses her love for Venky to him. Venky, who does not want to spoil the relationship between their parents, decides to leave the house, but Murthy goes to the railway station and talks to Venky, which makes Venky return. On his return, Nandu stops talking to him. When Venky accompanies Nandu and Pinky (Nandu's cousin) to Nandu's friend Asha's wedding, sparks fly between them. Even though Venky is also in love with Nandu, he does not express it and pretends that he did not have any feelings for Nandu. When they return, it is time for Nandu's wedding. Venky takes the onus of running the show of marriage. The demure Nandu is shattered. Circumstances lead to everyone finding out about Venky and Nandu. What follows, and how Nandu and Venky end up together, forms the climax of the story.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n* [[Daggubati Venkatesh|Venkatesh]] as Venky\n* [[Aarthi Agarwal]] as Nandini / Nandu(Voice dubbed by [[Savitha Reddy]])\n* [[Prakash Raj]] as Srinivasa Murthy\n* [[Sudha (Telugu actress)|Sudha]] as Lakshmi\n* [[Sudeepa Pinky]] as Pinky, Nandu's Cousin\n* [[Brahmanandam]] as Photographer\n* [[Sunil (actor)|Sunil]] as Banthi\n* [[Tanikella Bharani]] as Ashok\n* [[Chandra Mohan (Telugu actor)|Chandra Mohan]] as Shekaram\n* [[M. S. Narayana]] as Chanti\n* [[Babloo Prithiveeraj]] as Mohan\n* [[Shiju]] as Prasad, Nandu's fianc\u00e9\n* [[Shankar Melkote|Melkote]] as M.D.\n* [[Babu Mohan]] as Prasad's relative\n* [[Mallikarjuna Rao (actor)|Mallikarjuna Rao]] as Prasad's relative\n* [[Ananth Babu|Ananth]] as Asha's uncle\n* [[Chitti Babu Punyamurthula|Chitti Babu]] as Priest\n* [[Bandla Ganesh]] as Mohan's friend\n* [[Giridhar]] as Venky's friend\n* [[KK Sarma]] as Priest\n* [[Asha Saini]] as Asha\n* [[Suhasini Maniratnam|Suhasini]] as Sujatha\n* [[Sri Lakshmi (actress)|Sri Lakshmi]] as Asha's aunty\n* [[Hema (actress)|Hema]] as Padma\n* [[Padma Jayanthi]] as Prasad's mother\n* [[Kalpana Rai]] as Cook\n}}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Nuvvu Naaku Nachchav\n| type       = film\n| artist     = [[Saluri Koteswara Rao|Koti]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 2001\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = Soundtrack\n| length     = 29:17\n| label      = [[Aditya Music]]\n| producer   = [[Saluri Koteswara Rao|Koti]]\n| prev_title = [[Naalo Unna Prema]]\n| prev_year  = 2001\n| next_title = [[Adhipathi]]\n| next_year  = 2001\n}}\n\nMusic composed by [[Saluri Koteswara Rao|Koti]]. Music release