{"title_page": "Davi Ramos", "text_new": "{{short description|Brazilian MMA fighter}}\n{{Infobox martial artist\n| name            = Davi Ramos Pinheiro da Silva\n| other_names     = The Tasmanian Devil\n| image           =\n| image_size      =\n| alt             =\n| caption         =\n| birth_name      =\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1986|11|05}}\n| birth_place     = [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]\n| death_date      = \n| death_place     =\n| death_cause     =\n| residence       =\n| nationality     =  [[Brazilian people|Brazilian]]\n| height          = {{height|ft=5|in=6}}\n| weight          = {{convert|156|lb|kg st|abbr=on}}\n| weight_class    = [[Lightweight (MMA)|Lightweight]]\n| reach_in        = 72+1/2\n| style           = [[Brazilian Jiu Jitsu]]\n| stance          = \n| fighting_out_of = [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]\n| team            = Team Nogueira\n| rank            = 3rd degree<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uajiujitsu.com/about-us/|title=About Us - Ultimate Athlete Jiu-Jitsu - Modesto,CA|publisher=uajiujitsu.com|accessdate=May 19, 2019}}</ref> black belt in [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]] <small>under C\u00e9sar \"Casquinha\" Guimar\u00e3es</small><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bjjheroes.com/bjj-fighters/davi-ramos|title=Davi Ramos - BJJ Heroes|publisher=bjjheroes.com|accessdate=May 19, 2019}}</ref>\n| years_active    = 2010\u2013''present''\n| mma_kowin       = 1\n| mma_subwin      = 7\n| mma_decwin      = 2\n| mma_koloss      = \n| mma_otherwin    = \n| mma_subloss     = \n| mma_decloss     = 3\n| mma_draw        = \n| mma_nc          = \n| url             =\n| sherdog         = 101995\n| footnotes       =\n| updated         =\n|medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry|{{BRA}}}}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[Grappling]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[ADCC Submission Wrestling World Championship|ADCC World Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold | 2015 [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] | -77kg}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[ADCC_Submission_Wrestling_World_Championship#ADCC_South_American_Championship|ADCC South American Championships]]}} \n{{MedalGold | 2014 [[Rio de Janeiro]] | -77kg}}\n}}\n\n'''Davi Ramos''' (born November 5, 1986) is a Brazilian professional [[Mixed martial arts|mixed martial artist]] and [[Brazilian jiu-jitsu|Brazilian jiu jitsu]] practitioner. He competes in the [[Lightweight (MMA)|Lightweight]] division of the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]].\n\n==Grappling==\nRamos was the [[Grapplers Quest]] Lightweight and Absolute Division Champion in 2011 and the [[ADCC Submission Wrestling World Championship|ADCC]] Champion in 2015.\n\n==Mixed martial arts career==\n===Early career===\nRamos made his professional MMA debut in July 2010. Over the next six years, he amassed a record of 6 wins against 1 defeat.\n\n===Ultimate Fighting Championship===\nRamos made his UFC debut in March 2017 as a replacement for [[Max Griffin (fighter)|Max Griffin]] against [[S\u00e9rgio Moraes]] at [[UFC Fight Night: Belfort vs. Gastelum]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sportv.globo.com/site/combate/noticia/2017/03/ufc-convoca-davi-ramos-para-enfrentar-serginho-em-fortaleza.html|title=UFC calls up David Ramos to face Serginho in Fortaleza|publisher=sportv.globo.com|author=Marcelo Barone and Raphael Marinho|accessdate=2017-03-04|date=2017-03-04|language=pt}}</ref> He lost the fight via unanimous decision.\n\nIn his second fight for the promotion, Ramos faced [[Chris Gruetzemacher]] on December 9, 2017 at [[UFC Fight Night: Swanson vs. Ortega]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ufc.com/event/ufc-fight-night-fresno-dec-9-2017#/fight|title=UFC Fight Night: Swanson vs. Ortega|publisher=Ultimate Fighting Championship|accessdate=2017-09-28}}</ref> He won the fight via rear-naked choke submission in the third round.\n\nFor his third fight with the promotion, Ramos faced [[Nick Hein]] on May 12, 2018 at [[UFC 224]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ufc.com/event/Ufc-224|title=UFC 224: Nunes vs. Pennington|publisher=Ultimate Fighting Championship|accessdate=2018-02-04}}</ref> He won the fight via rear-naked choke submission in the first round.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mmajunkie.com/2018/05/ufc-224-results-davi-ramos-fantastic-on-the-floor-finishes-nick-hein-in-first|title=UFC 224 results: Davi Ramos fantastic on the floor, finishes Nick Hein in first|date=2018-05-13|work=MMAjunkie|access-date=2018-05-13|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nRamos faced John Gunther on November 10, 2018 at [[UFC Fight Night 139]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmadna.nl/bjj-wizard-davi-ramos-treft-de-ongeslagen-john-gunther-tijdens-ufc-denver/|title=BJJ wizard Davi Ramos meets the unbeaten John Gunther at UFC Denver|publisher=mmadna.nl|author=Marcel Dorff|date=2018-09-20|accessdate=2018-09-20|language=nl}}</ref> He won the fight via a rear-naked choke in round one.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://cagesidepress.com/2018/11/10/ufc-denver-results-davi-ramos-chokes-out-john-gunther/|title=UFC Denver Results: Davi Ramos Chokes Out John Gunther|last=Evanoff|first=Josh|date=2018-11-10|work=Cageside Press|access-date=2018-11-11|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nRamos faced promotional newcomer [[Austin Hubbard]] on May 18, 2019 at [[UFC Fight Night 152]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mmadna.nl/davi-ramos-treft-ufc-debutant-en-lfa-kampioen-austin-hubbard-tijdens-ufc-rochester/|title=Davi Ramos meets UFC rookie and LFA Champion Austin Hubbard during UFC Rochester|publisher=mmadna.nl|author=Marcel Dorff|date=2019-04-09|access-date=2019-04-09|language=nl}}</ref> He won the fight via unanimous decision.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cagesidepress.com/2019/05/18/ufc-rochester-results-davi-ramos-dominates-austin-hubbard-decision/|title=UFC Rochester Results: Davi Ramos Dominates Austin Hubbard in Unanimous Decision Victory|last=Bitter|first=Shawn|date=2019-05-18|website=Cageside Press|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-19}}</ref>\n\nRamos faced [[Islam Makhachev]] on September 7, 2019 at [[UFC 242]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmarocks.pl/islam-makhachev/islam-makachaev-vs-davi-ramos-na-ufc-242|title=Islam Makhachev Vs. Davi Ramos at UFC 242|author=Bart\u0142omiej Zubkiewicz|publisher=mmarocks.pl|date=2019-06-07|access-date=2019-06-07|language=pl}}</ref> He lost the fight via unanimous decision.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cagesidepress.com/2019/09/07/ufc-242-results-islam-makhachev/|title=UFC 242 Results: Islam Makhachev Nearly Finishes Davi Ramos in Underwhelming Fight|last=Doherty|first=Dan|date=2019-09-07|website=Cageside Press|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-07}}</ref>\n\nRamos is expected to face Arman Tsarukyan on April 11, 2020 at [[UFC Fight Night 172]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mmadna.nl/davi-ramos-vs-arman-tsarukyan-toegevoegd-aan-ufc-portland/|title=Davi Ramos vs. Arman Tsarukyan added to UFC Portland|author=Redactie|publisher=mmadna.nl|date=2020-03-04|access-date=2020-03-04}}{{in lang|nl}}</ref> Due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], the event was eventually postponed .<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mmajunkie.usatoday.com/2020/03/ufc-postpones-three-events-coronavirus-pandemic|title=UFC postpones three events amid growing coronavirus outbreak|publisher=mmajunkie.usatoday.com|author=Nolan King and John Morgan|date=2020-03-15|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\n==Mixed martial arts record==\n{{MMArecordbox\n| draws= \n| nc= \n| ko-wins= 1\n| sub-wins= 7\n| dec-wins= 2\n| ko-losses= \n| sub-losses= \n| dec-losses= 3\n| dq-wins= \n| dq-losses= \n| other-wins= \n| other-losses= \n}}\n{{MMA record start}}\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center|10\u20133\n|[[Islam Makhachev]]\n|Decision (unanimous)\n|[[UFC 242]] \n|{{dts|2019|September|7}}\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|5:00\n|[[Abu Dhabi]], United Arab Emirates\n|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|align=center|10\u20132\n|[[Austin Hubbard]]\n|Decision (unanimous)\n|[[UFC Fight Night: dos Anjos vs. Lee]] \n|{{dts|2019|May|18}}\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|5:00\n|[[Rochester, New York]], United States\n|\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n|align=center| 9\u20132\n|John Gunther\n|Submission (rear-naked choke)\n|[[UFC Fight Night: